  <p>
    This project trains a <b>K-Nearest Neighbors</b> (KNN) classifier on the classic
    <b>Iris</b> dataset to predict flower species from 4 measurements:
    sepal length/width and petal length/width.
  </p>

  <h2>Method (short)</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Load dataset (scikit-learn).</li>
    <li>Train/test split (80/20).</li>
    <li>Scale features with StandardScaler.</li>
    <li>Train KNN (k=3) and evaluate accuracy + confusion matrix.</li>
    <li>Visualize sepal length vs. width.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Run locally</h2>
  <pre>
pip install pandas scikit-learn matplotlib
python3 iris_classification.py
  </pre>

